    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ 395\u00b0F/ Gas 6</p><p>Peel and dice the <strong>red onions </strong>(as finely as you can!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion\u00a0</strong>with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and cook for 10-12 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong>\u00a0basmati rice</strong>\u00a0and 300ml [600ml] <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once\u00a0done, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p><p>Tip: Add a knob of butter once cooked for extra indulgence</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop the\u00a0<strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop the\u00a0<strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped\u00a0garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>ground\u00a0coriander</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes, cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0to a<strong> pestle\u00a0& mortar</strong>\u00a0and grind to a smooth paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\">\u00a0[4 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong>\u00a0balch\u00e3o spice paste</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively, use a food processor!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>balch\u00e3o spice paste</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 4-5 min\u00a0or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> plain naans </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>\u00a0king prawns</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste</strong>,\u00a0<strong>cider vinegar</strong>\u00a0and 1 tsp\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the prawns are almost cooked through</p><p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong>\u00a0with 60ml<span class=\"text-danger\">\u00a0[100ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>\u00a0and cook for a further 2-3 min or until the spinach has just wilted and the sauce is\u00a0thickened to a curry-like consistency \u2013 this is your<strong> Goan prawn balch\u00e3o curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-prawn-balchao-curry-with-basmati-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the\u00a0<strong>Goan prawn balch\u00e3o curry</strong> over the<strong> basmati rice</strong> with the <strong>warmed naan</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
